.TH "ATOMIC\-GC" "8" "" "atomic\-upgrade" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
atomic\-gc \[em] manage atomic\-upgrade generations
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]atomic\-gc\f[R] [\f[B]\-n\f[R]|\f[B]\-\-dry\-run\f[R]]
[\f[I]COUNT\f[R]]
.PP
\f[B]atomic\-gc\f[R] \f[B]list\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]atomic\-gc\f[R] \f[B]rm\f[R] [\f[B]\-n\f[R]|\f[B]\-\-dry\-run\f[R]]
[\f[B]\-y\f[R]|\f[B]\-\-yes\f[R]] \f[I]GEN_ID\f[R]
[\f[I]GEN_ID\f[R]\&...]
.PP
\f[B]atomic\-gc\f[R] \f[B]activate\f[R] \f[I]GEN_ID\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]atomic\-gc\f[R] \f[B]deactivate\f[R] \f[I]GEN_ID\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]atomic\-gc\f[R] \f[B]protect\f[R] \f[I]GEN_ID\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]atomic\-gc\f[R] \f[B]unprotect\f[R] \f[I]GEN_ID\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]atomic\-gc\f[R] manages generations created by
\f[B]atomic\-upgrade\f[R](8).
A generation consists of a Btrfs subvolume (\f[I]root\-TIMESTAMP\f[R])
and a matching UKI file on the ESP (\f[I]arch\-TIMESTAMP.efi\f[R]).
.PP
Without a subcommand, \f[B]atomic\-gc\f[R] runs garbage collection:
keeps the last \f[I]COUNT\f[R] generations (default from
\f[B]KEEP_GENERATIONS\f[R] in \f[B]atomic.conf\f[R](5)) plus the
currently booted one, and deletes the rest.
After deletion, an orphan sweep removes:
.IP \[bu] 2
Subvolumes that have no matching UKI on the ESP.
.IP \[bu] 2
UKI files that have no matching subvolume.
.PP
Orphan \f[I]home\-*\f[R] subvolumes (created by
\f[B]\-\-separate\-home\f[R]) are \f[B]reported but never
auto\-deleted\f[R] \[em] they may contain user data.
A message with the manual deletion command is printed for each orphan.
.PP
If the ESP is not mounted during the orphan sweep, it is skipped with a
warning.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
\f[B](none)\f[R] [\f[I]COUNT\f[R]]
Run garbage collection.
\f[I]COUNT\f[R] overrides the configured \f[B]KEEP_GENERATIONS\f[R]
value.
Requires root.
.TP
\f[B]list\f[R]
List all generations found on the ESP, newest first.
The currently booted generation is marked with \f[B](current)\f[R].
Does not require root.
.TP
\f[B]rm\f[R] \f[I]GEN_ID\f[R] [\f[I]GEN_ID\f[R]\&...]
Delete specific generation(s).
Removes both the UKI file and the Btrfs subvolume.
Refuses to delete the currently booted or protected generation.
Prompts for confirmation unless \f[B]\-y\f[R] is given.
Requires root.
.TP
\f[B]activate\f[R] \f[I]GEN_ID\f[R]
Mark a generation as active by adding a \f[CR]0\-active\-\f[R] prefix to
its UKI file.
The UEFI firmware loads files alphabetically, so this forces the
generation to boot first.
Requires root.
.TP
\f[B]deactivate\f[R] \f[I]GEN_ID\f[R]
Remove the active marker from a generation.
Renames the UKI file by removing the \f[CR]0\-active\-\f[R] prefix.
Requires root.
.TP
\f[B]protect\f[R] \f[I]GEN_ID\f[R]
Protect a generation from garbage collection by creating a sidecar file
(\f[CR]arch\-GEN_ID.efi.protected\f[R]).
Protected generations are skipped during garbage collection.
Requires root.
.TP
\f[B]unprotect\f[R] \f[I]GEN_ID\f[R]
Remove protection from a generation by deleting its
\f[CR].protected\f[R] sidecar file.
Requires root.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-n\f[R], \f[B]\-\-dry\-run\f[R]
Show what would be deleted without making changes.
.TP
\f[B]\-y\f[R], \f[B]\-\-yes\f[R]
Skip confirmation prompt (for \f[B]rm\f[R] subcommand only).
.TP
\f[B]\-V\f[R], \f[B]\-\-version\f[R]
Show version and exit.
.TP
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\-\-help\f[R]
Show usage summary and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
Success.
.TP
\f[B]1\f[R]
Error.
Common causes: generation not found, attempted deletion of current
generation, lock held by another instance.
.SH EXAMPLES
Garbage collect using configured default:
.IP
.EX
sudo atomic\-gc
.EE
.PP
Preview keeping only the last 2 generations:
.IP
.EX
sudo atomic\-gc \-\-dry\-run 2
.EE
.PP
List all generations:
.IP
.EX
atomic\-gc list
.EE
.PP
Delete a specific generation:
.IP
.EX
sudo atomic\-gc rm 20260217\-143022
.EE
.PP
Delete multiple generations without confirmation:
.IP
.EX
sudo atomic\-gc rm \-y 20260217\-143022 20260216\-235122
.EE
.PP
Mark a generation as active (boots first):
.IP
.EX
sudo atomic\-gc activate 20260217\-143022
.EE
.PP
Remove active marker:
.IP
.EX
sudo atomic\-gc deactivate 20260217\-143022
.EE
.PP
Protect a generation from GC:
.IP
.EX
sudo atomic\-gc protect 20260217\-143022
.EE
.PP
Remove protection:
.IP
.EX
sudo atomic\-gc unprotect 20260217\-143022
.EE
